<document>
    <properties>
        <title>Authentication</title>
    </properties>
    <body>
        <section name="Repository based authentication">
        <span class='shortdesc'>Authentication with The Repository Login Module</span>
        <p>
            The repository stores the users and groups as nodes inside the repository itself.
            The HippoLoginModule is configured in
            <a href="index.html#Security_element"><code>repository.xml</code></a> in the Security section and is enabled be default.
        </p>
<source>
&lt;LoginModule class="org.hippoecm.repository.security.HippoLoginModule"/&gt;
</source>
        <p>
            The authentication module is based on
            <a href="http://java.sun.com/j2se/1.5.0/docs/guide/security/jaas/JAASRefGuide.html" title="Sun JAAS">JAAS</a>.
        </p>
        <p>
            For more information on how the users and groups are stored see the <a href="../nodes/users.html">Users</a> and <a href="../nodes/users.html">Groups</a> nodes configuration section.
        </p>
        </section>
    </body>
</document>
